Detailed Description

A basic root-level object definition.

This definition is extremely similar to the Java Object class and allows subclasses to more-closely follow their Java counterparts.

virtual bool vrt::VRTObject::equals ( const VRTObject *  o  )  const [virtual]

Tests this object for equality with another one.



Since this function was added *after* the one that takes in a reference, the default implementation is: 

    bool VRTObject::equals (const VRTObject *o) const {
      return (o != NULL) && equals(*o);
    }
Parameters:
o The unknown object.
Returns:
true if they are identical, false otherwise.
